<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee20b41f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s228d"><num value="228d">§ 228d.</num><heading> Annual assessment of cattle and hog industries</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than March 1 of each year, the Secretary shall submit to Congress and make publicly available a report that—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee20b420-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s228d/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> assesses the general economic state of the cattle and hog industries;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee20b421-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s228d/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> describes changing business practices in those industries; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee20b422-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s228d/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> identifies market operations or activities in those industries that appear to raise concerns under this chapter.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idee20b423-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1921-08-15/ch64">Aug. 15, 1921, ch. 64</ref>, title IV, § 415, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/472/tIII/s312/e/2">Pub. L. 106–472, title III, § 312(e)(2)</ref>, <date date="2000-11-09">Nov. 9, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2077">114 Stat. 2077</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idee20b424-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idee20b425-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="idee20b426-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior section 415 of act <date date="1921-08-15">Aug. 15, 1921</date>, was renumbered section 417 and is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s229c">section 229c of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
